# Step 7 – First Sub-Strategy: Market-Making Mode (Depth ***)

**Only implement Step 7 (Market-Making Mode).**  
Do not touch any other sub-strategies yet. We will add the others one by one after this is verified.

### Overall Goal of Step 7.1
Add the **Market-Making Mode** as the first full sub-strategy.

This is the default “chill” mode: place tight limit orders on both sides of the current mid-price to earn the spread, while staying perfectly balanced.

The strategy must integrate cleanly with:
- The permanent micro-layer (from Step 6)
- The main brain (future Step 8)
- The new botLogger (from Step 5)
- The steem-like connector (from Step 2)

### Exact Behaviour Required (Market-Making Mode)

- Place **tight limit orders** on both sides of the current DEX mid-price:
  - Bid: 0.4–0.6% below mid
  - Ask: 0.4–0.6% above mid
- Use small but reasonable size (configurable, default ~2–5 SBD worth per side)
- When one side is filled → immediately replace it on the **same side** at the same distance to stay balanced
- Refresh/cancel stale orders every 30–45 seconds
- The mode is **active by default** when the bot starts (unless config disables it)
- Respect the micro-layer: never cancel or interfere with the tiny inverted-pyramid orders

### Integration & Control
- Create `strategies/market-making/index.js` following the exact strategy contract:
  - `init(config)`
  - `tick(config)` (called periodically by the engine)
  - `shutdown(config)`
  - `describe()`
- The main bot `index.js` must be able to start/stop this strategy via the engine/runner
- Use `botLog()` for every placement, fill, and mode change (eventType: "MARKET_MAKING_PLACED", "MARKET_MAKING_FILLED", etc.)
- Update the dashboard with a new **“Active Strategy”** section showing:
  - Current mode name
  - Number of active market-making orders
  - Last fill time

